Niger Gets $122 Million Loans to Cut Poverty, Accelerate Political Reform

-- B y   D j i b r i l   S a i d o u
-- 
2011-07-15T12:08:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-15/niger-gets-122-million-loans-to-cut-poverty-accelerate-political-reform.html
Niger secured two loans worth a
combined $122 million from the  World Bank  to fund projects aimed
at reducing poverty and accelerating political reform in the
West African nation, Amadou Boubacar Cisse, the Minister of
Community Development, told reporters today in the capital,
Niamey.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  